## Definition of Done & Final Handoff
Do not declare a session or task DONE until `docs/CLOSING_CHECKLIST.md` has been executed.

When the operator says "run the closing checklist", "run closeout", asks if everything is done, or when you believe the task is complete, load `docs/CLOSING_CHECKLIST.md`, complete its Closing Gate table, and use its required final handoff shape.

If any required closing-checklist item is FAIL, do not claim DONE. Report what is blocked and the exact next action needed.